cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for continuous sign language recognition using deep learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The proposed method involves structured feature extraction and encoding, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses two large-scale public datasets for evaluation, indicating that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
